      <hedline>
        <hl1>Green Cities</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jane Phillips letter says increased gas taxes should be spent on developing better mass transit</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Gas Pump Geopolitics'' (column, April 28):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Gas Pump Geopolitics'' (column, April 28):</p>
        <p>One suggestion I would add to Thomas L. Friedman's energy policy recommendations is that the increased gas taxes be spent on developing better mass transit across the nation.</p>
        <p>Most American cities, except for the larger ones, give commuters no choice but to drive. A rail system, like Europe's, would not only relieve the burden of high gas prices on the poor but would also give all commuters the option to sit back, read the news and be green.</p>
        <p>And the walk to and from the station wouldn't hurt us at all.</p>
        <p>Jane Phillips  Columbia, Mo., April 28, 2006</p>
      </block>
